LAGOS – Temitope Odunlami, an Abeokuta-based gospel singer popularly known as Ijo Ope is set to praise the Lord with danceable gospel tunes. The January edition of the open ground monthly gospel music fiesta tagged: “An Hour Street Praise” is scheduled to hold on Tuesday 4 at the open space opposite Elite road junction. Temitope Odunlami, in a chat with Daily Independent, said the January edition is the first in the year promises to be spiritually uplifting and full of praises to Almighty God our creator. Abeokuta 10km Race: Organizers Promise Prompt Payment Of Prize… 3,500 Receive Free Eye Treatment, Cataract Surgeries In Ogun “It is time of the month to praise God for his protection, love, and guardians over the country, our state, local government, communities and our homes individually and collectively. ” What else can we give to the Lord that has preserved and saved our families from the dangers of the world all through the year 2021. My creator deserved to be praised, hallelujah,” she added. The artist disclosed that the street praise will feature a special presentation by Olori Iyabode Gbadebo.